1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:39,075 --> 00:00:40,545
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

3
00:00:40,545 --> 00:00:41,975
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:42,815 --> 00:00:43,885
The hospital?

5
00:00:44,615 --> 00:00:47,685
I just got her admitted.
And I have to pick up things for Momo.

6
00:00:48,385 --> 00:00:50,755
Then come to the Gangnam Hotel.
Let's get breakfast.

7
00:00:51,385 --> 00:00:52,625
Don't you have a morning flight?

8
00:00:56,625 --> 00:00:57,965
When did you get vertigo?

9
00:00:58,895 --> 00:01:00,165
Not long ago.

10
00:01:00,935 --> 00:01:02,805
How did you end up with Ju Shin?

11
00:01:04,435 --> 00:01:06,705
Director Shin gave me a ride after dinner.

12
00:01:07,105 --> 00:01:09,045
I suddenly got so dizzy
that I just sank to the ground.

13
00:01:09,345 --> 00:01:11,405
Don't get too close to Ju Shin.

14
00:01:12,545 --> 00:01:13,975
Keep him at arm's length.

15
00:01:15,375 --> 00:01:16,385
Why?

16
00:01:17,185 --> 00:01:18,285
You saw what happened with Momo.

17
00:01:18,685 --> 00:01:20,215
The guy's pretty heartless
when it comes to women.

18
00:01:22,585 --> 00:01:24,955
I thought you were asking me to breakfast
because you were worried...

19
00:01:25,385 --> 00:01:26,395
about Momo.

20
00:02:10,535 --> 00:02:12,935
(Red Bean Rice Cakes)

21
00:02:15,845 --> 00:02:17,875
I hope it doesn't rain in Jeju.

22
00:02:18,605 --> 00:02:19,615
Let's see...

23
00:02:20,715 --> 00:02:23,345
Your dad finally got to take his staff
to Jeju.

24
00:02:24,515 --> 00:02:26,955
Man, I could really go for
some red bean rice cakes.

25
00:02:36,895 --> 00:02:39,165
(Yong Joong)

26
00:02:40,335 --> 00:02:42,635
We had just gotten to the hotel in Jeju
and were unpacking...

27
00:02:42,905 --> 00:02:44,105
when we heard
the father of the head of marketing...

28
00:02:44,105 --> 00:02:45,205
had passed away.

29
00:02:45,635 --> 00:02:46,635
Did he have a chronic condition?

30
00:02:46,975 --> 00:02:48,705
No. Just high blood pressure.

31
00:02:49,075 --> 00:02:50,175
High blood pressure is chronic.

32
00:02:51,745 --> 00:02:53,075
Good to see you both. It's been a while.

33
00:03:17,735 --> 00:03:19,705
(Red Bean Rice Cakes)

34
00:03:20,135 --> 00:03:21,875
(Red Bean Rice Cakes)

35
00:03:25,045 --> 00:03:26,045
Are you and Ba Ra dating?

36
00:03:26,915 --> 00:03:28,245
We're not quite at that stage yet.

37
00:03:29,685 --> 00:03:31,945
I'm thinking of skipping the dating
and going straight to marriage.

38
00:03:33,655 --> 00:03:34,715
I already proposed.

39
00:03:35,855 --> 00:03:36,885
What were you thinking?

40
00:03:37,755 --> 00:03:39,195
You just called off your wedding.

41
00:03:40,155 --> 00:03:41,955
What does time have to do with it?

42
00:03:42,995 --> 00:03:44,365
You can fall for someone in an instant...

43
00:03:45,595 --> 00:03:47,035
and fall out of love just as quickly.

44
00:03:49,635 --> 00:03:50,735
So, what did Ba Ra say?

45
00:04:18,525 --> 00:04:19,535
It's really coming down.

46
00:04:28,005 --> 00:04:29,005
You need to be less jumpy.

47
00:04:29,905 --> 00:04:31,345
I can't come running every time.

48
00:04:33,275 --> 00:04:34,415
Thank you.

49
00:04:37,285 --> 00:04:38,315
You should go now.

50
00:04:39,355 --> 00:04:40,685
I told you not to thank me.

51
00:04:43,325 --> 00:04:44,325
Are you sulking?

52
00:04:46,395 --> 00:04:47,955
Why would I sulk at you?

53
00:04:48,055 --> 00:04:50,295
What do you mean, "why"?
I've decided to marry you.

54
00:04:53,865 --> 00:04:56,305
I just feel bad that
you're the second person I've asked.

55
00:04:58,335 --> 00:05:00,135
Please, don't even think about it.

56
00:05:00,835 --> 00:05:02,035
I can think whatever I want.

57
00:05:02,845 --> 00:05:04,545
If you keep this up,
I can't be comfortable around you.

58
00:05:08,275 --> 00:05:09,285
Do you have any ramyeon?

59
00:05:12,115 --> 00:05:13,715
Isn't that the popular line these days?
"Want to stay for ramyeon?"

60
00:05:15,755 --> 00:05:17,285
Did you see that on TV?

61
00:05:18,625 --> 00:05:19,955
I heard the nurses talking about it.

62
00:05:22,625 --> 00:05:24,125
Didn't you eat dinner?

63
00:05:24,525 --> 00:05:25,525
No.

64
00:05:29,435 --> 00:05:30,905
Gosh, how embarrassing.

65
00:05:32,105 --> 00:05:35,635
What's embarrassing?
You're not exactly the timid type.

66
00:05:40,445 --> 00:05:41,875
Just stay in the car.

67
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:50,625
Don't you have an umbrella in the trunk?

68
00:05:50,925 --> 00:05:52,425
I don't know. Can't be bothered.

69
00:05:54,295 --> 00:05:56,165
Please remove your card.

70
00:05:58,325 --> 00:05:59,965
I didn't even know this place existed.

71
00:06:00,095 --> 00:06:01,395
You never noticed it driving by?

72
00:06:01,765 --> 00:06:03,135
I'm usually asleep in the car.

73
00:06:03,405 --> 00:06:04,705
You sound like an old man.

74
00:06:05,535 --> 00:06:07,075
I like getting the senior treatment.

75
00:06:07,705 --> 00:06:08,735
I'll do it for you.

76
00:06:10,375 --> 00:06:11,375
Do you eat bean sprouts?

77
00:06:12,615 --> 00:06:13,745
I'm not a big fan of toppings.

78
00:06:14,745 --> 00:06:15,745
Not even an egg?

79
00:06:17,345 --> 00:06:19,885
(Regular Noodles)

80
00:06:26,155 --> 00:06:27,855
These days, it's not "ramyeon."

81
00:06:27,955 --> 00:06:29,465
It's "Want to come up and watch a show?"

82
00:06:29,625 --> 00:06:32,125
Or, "Want to come up and see my cat?"
That's what they say now.

83
00:06:32,795 --> 00:06:33,995
Oh, Pickles.

84
00:06:34,735 --> 00:06:36,465
James is looking after him for me.

85
00:06:37,565 --> 00:06:40,405
He was really heartbroken
after Oiji crossed the rainbow bridge.

86
00:06:40,675 --> 00:06:42,305
So he likes seeing him from time to time.

87
00:06:43,075 --> 00:06:44,375
Everything dies.

88
00:06:46,415 --> 00:06:48,475
It's a bit of an exaggeration,
but I deal with it almost every day.

89
00:06:50,085 --> 00:06:51,345
There's no point in getting attached.

90
00:06:52,345 --> 00:06:55,485
- So that means...
- Don't lecture me.

91
00:06:56,985 --> 00:06:58,085
The same goes for you.

92
00:06:59,355 --> 00:07:00,795
Do you always have to have the last word?

93
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:03,495
It's so you get sick of it.

94
00:07:07,995 --> 00:07:09,265
Let's go to James's after we eat.

95
00:07:09,635 --> 00:07:12,735
- Don't you want to see Pickles?
- It's almost 10 p.m.

96
00:07:12,975 --> 00:07:14,405
James doesn't go to bed
until after midnight.

97
00:07:14,775 --> 00:07:15,775
He has insomnia.

98
00:07:18,045 --> 00:07:21,015
Besides,
I'm curious about the furball myself.

99
00:07:22,415 --> 00:07:23,445
That's a good thing.

100
00:07:26,585 --> 00:07:29,555
You must be cold.
What if you catch a cold?

101
00:07:29,655 --> 00:07:31,125
Then you can come make me
some bean sprout soup.

102
00:07:35,965 --> 00:07:36,995
I'm serious.

103
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:40,265
I'll make it for you.

104
00:07:50,645 --> 00:07:51,705
Does it taste okay?

105
00:07:52,005 --> 00:07:53,015
It's delicious.

106
00:07:54,415 --> 00:07:56,345
You handle hot food better
than I expected.

107
00:07:57,015 --> 00:07:59,885
A surprising number of male reporters
can't handle hot food.

108
00:08:00,785 --> 00:08:02,385
Ramyeon's no good when it gets cold.

109
00:08:05,025 --> 00:08:06,625
Our food tastes are compatible too.

110
00:08:08,625 --> 00:08:10,895
How about some ice cream for dessert?

111
00:08:11,195 --> 00:08:12,535
I saw they had those
squeeze-up ones, right?

112
00:08:13,235 --> 00:08:14,635
Might as well let you
treat me to dessert, too.

113
00:08:15,595 --> 00:08:16,605
Okay.

114
00:08:23,545 --> 00:08:24,745
What's the coffee-flavored one like?

115
00:08:26,475 --> 00:08:27,845
It tastes like sweet coffee.

116
00:08:30,415 --> 00:08:31,615
Just save me a bite.

117
00:08:32,185 --> 00:08:34,055
I'm already soaked.
How am I supposed to eat two of these?

118
00:08:34,555 --> 00:08:36,325
I'll finish it if you don't.

119
00:08:38,285 --> 00:08:40,295
But I thought you liked being treated.

120
00:08:40,595 --> 00:08:41,895
That's not the kind of treatment
I had in mind.

121
00:08:47,065 --> 00:08:48,435
You're the one
who's going to catch a cold.

122
00:08:50,105 --> 00:08:51,535
You're not a germaphobe?

123
00:08:52,575 --> 00:08:53,575
It won't kill me.

124
00:08:53,975 --> 00:08:55,535
Besides,
it's good to share beneficial bacteria.

125
00:09:08,685 --> 00:09:09,685
Hey, James, it's me.

126
00:09:10,425 --> 00:09:11,455
You picked up right away.

127
00:09:13,625 --> 00:09:15,055
Can I swing by for a bit?

128
00:09:16,595 --> 00:09:17,595
Yes.

129
00:09:19,165 --> 00:09:21,765
I'm not going. It's an imposition.

130
00:09:26,705 --> 00:09:29,845
What's he going to think
if we show up together this late?

131
00:09:31,105 --> 00:09:32,575
He'll probably think we're dating.

132
00:09:35,075 --> 00:09:37,215
I don't need to see Pickles.

133
00:09:38,285 --> 00:09:39,315
But I want to see him.

134
00:09:40,085 --> 00:09:41,615
He's probably going to think
you abandoned him.

135
00:09:43,455 --> 00:09:44,525
It's a she.

136
00:09:46,025 --> 00:09:47,095
She's a female?

137
00:09:48,125 --> 00:09:49,125
Yes.

138
00:09:51,125 --> 00:09:52,525
That's a crude way to put it.

139
00:09:53,565 --> 00:09:56,105
Should I call her "young girl"
or "young lady"?

140
00:09:57,035 --> 00:09:58,165
Is "female dog" any better?

141
00:09:59,165 --> 00:10:00,175
Actually,

142
00:10:00,805 --> 00:10:04,945
calling yourself a pet's "mom" or "dad"
is a bit much.

143
00:10:05,275 --> 00:10:06,275
True.

144
00:10:07,275 --> 00:10:09,215
People raise dogs instead of having kids.

145
00:10:09,585 --> 00:10:12,015
I'd be perfectly happy
just living with Pickles.

146
00:10:14,785 --> 00:10:16,355
Do you have any ginger tea or anything?

147
00:10:17,185 --> 00:10:18,185
No.

148
00:10:18,755 --> 00:10:19,855
I do at my place.

149
00:10:20,655 --> 00:10:24,195
I just sneezed because of the change
in temperature.

150
00:10:25,965 --> 00:10:27,035
When it rains,

151
00:10:28,095 --> 00:10:30,835
don't draw the curtains and hide in fear.
Just watch it.

152
00:10:33,035 --> 00:10:35,705
If you watch, you'll see it's not scary.
It's actually refreshing.

153
00:10:41,975 --> 00:10:43,445
When I'm faced with hardship,

154
00:10:43,585 --> 00:10:45,715
I just say,
"Bring it on. I'll meet it head-on."

155
00:10:46,485 --> 00:10:47,485
I don't run from it.

156
00:10:53,695 --> 00:10:55,125
That's a different issue.

157
00:10:56,795 --> 00:10:57,895
It might be a different issue,

158
00:10:58,965 --> 00:11:00,665
but that's the attitude I live with.

159
00:11:01,865 --> 00:11:02,865
To live...

160
00:11:22,725 --> 00:11:24,355
Want to share some beneficial microbes?

161
00:11:28,595 --> 00:11:29,695
They're good for your immune system.

162
00:11:31,365 --> 00:11:32,595
Please be serious.

163
00:11:33,395 --> 00:11:34,665
I am being serious.

164
00:11:37,205 --> 00:11:38,665
You really don't see me as a man?

165
00:11:39,875 --> 00:11:42,335
I do. But that's a different issue.

166
00:11:45,105 --> 00:11:46,515
"A different issue," miss.

167
00:11:47,715 --> 00:11:48,945
I've grown to like you.

168
00:11:50,445 --> 00:11:52,015
I never expected it.

169
00:11:57,585 --> 00:12:00,455
So this is all I am to Yong Joong.

170
00:12:01,695 --> 00:12:03,365
With no romantic spark.

171
00:12:07,295 --> 00:12:08,365
I'll wait.

172
00:12:08,995 --> 00:12:11,205
You can't force feelings.

173
00:12:12,365 --> 00:12:13,435
Just not for too long.

174
00:12:16,845 --> 00:12:19,405
Don't let me celebrate my 60th birthday
as a lonely bachelor.

175
00:12:21,175 --> 00:12:23,445
These days,
people don't even celebrate turning 70.

176
00:12:29,355 --> 00:12:30,355
She shot me down.

177
00:12:31,385 --> 00:12:32,385
I saw it coming.

178
00:12:34,655 --> 00:12:35,955
You two aren't like siblings, are you?

179
00:12:36,625 --> 00:12:39,695
If she really saw you as a man,
she would've told you right away.

180
00:12:41,495 --> 00:12:43,335
She probably thought
it was better left unsaid.

181
00:12:44,335 --> 00:12:46,105
Because it's just too absurd.

182
00:12:51,205 --> 00:12:52,205
What about today?

183
00:12:53,215 --> 00:12:54,275
The rain was coming down so hard.

184
00:12:55,875 --> 00:12:57,085
And she mentioned
that she was scared of it.

185
00:12:58,515 --> 00:13:01,755
We also stopped by your brother's place
to see Pickles.

186
00:13:02,285 --> 00:13:04,625
Oh, my goodness! Come on in.

187
00:13:05,385 --> 00:13:07,325
I'm sorry to impose, but I tagged along.

188
00:13:07,325 --> 00:13:09,565
Nonsense! You're more than welcome!

189
00:13:09,965 --> 00:13:10,965
Pickles.

190
00:13:13,865 --> 00:13:15,465
What brings you two busy people here?

191
00:13:16,605 --> 00:13:17,605
Have you two had dinner?

192
00:13:17,935 --> 00:13:20,435
I thought her heart would be
trembling in fear, so I went to see her.

193
00:13:21,005 --> 00:13:22,375
And she ended up buying me ramyeon.

194
00:13:22,705 --> 00:13:23,805
What's wrong with her heart?

195
00:13:24,205 --> 00:13:25,205
He's kidding.

196
00:13:25,745 --> 00:13:29,785
He knows I'm afraid of thunderstorms,
so he stopped by since he was nearby.

197
00:13:30,445 --> 00:13:31,685
I guess she was a dog in a past life.

198
00:13:32,215 --> 00:13:33,485
What about you?

199
00:13:33,485 --> 00:13:34,685
- What was your past life...
- A deity.

200
00:13:36,925 --> 00:13:38,485
Ju as in "master," Shin as in "spirit."

201
00:13:38,485 --> 00:13:39,595
Let him dream.

202
00:13:40,325 --> 00:13:42,725
- Should I make some fried rice?
- I've had enough carbs for one day.

203
00:13:43,225 --> 00:13:45,565
- I'll grill some meat for you.
- We were just stopping by.

204
00:13:45,925 --> 00:13:47,935
They say dogs take after their owners,
so we were worried she'd be scared.

205
00:13:49,135 --> 00:13:50,365
Oh, she was.

206
00:13:51,265 --> 00:13:52,435
Does Yong Joong stop by often?

207
00:13:52,875 --> 00:13:54,235
He checks in on me whenever he can.

208
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:56,945
He treats me like an old man,
saying he doesn't age.

209
00:13:57,475 --> 00:13:58,705
He should be good to his older brother.

210
00:13:58,705 --> 00:14:01,545
I just wish he'd meet someone nice.

211
00:14:01,875 --> 00:14:03,485
But there's a proper order to things.

212
00:14:03,885 --> 00:14:07,115
- You have to get married first.
- Why don't you set me up with someone?

213
00:14:07,655 --> 00:14:09,085
You're always around female celebs...

214
00:14:09,085 --> 00:14:11,825
It's not like the young, beautiful celebs
are throwing themselves at me.

215
00:14:12,625 --> 00:14:13,995
And I can't just go and hit on them.

216
00:14:15,055 --> 00:14:16,225
They have to be young and beautiful,

217
00:14:16,795 --> 00:14:17,925
but they have to have beautiful minds too.

218
00:14:18,225 --> 00:14:19,225
Exactly.

219
00:14:22,095 --> 00:14:23,465
When is Yong Joong coming to Jeju?

220
00:14:24,205 --> 00:14:25,205
The day after tomorrow.

221
00:14:30,105 --> 00:14:31,445
I have a villa in Jeju.

222
00:14:32,475 --> 00:14:34,945
You should go and relax for a bit.
It's a shame for it to just sit empty.

223
00:14:37,585 --> 00:14:38,745
Maybe with me someday?

224
00:14:47,625 --> 00:14:49,355
Ba Ra isn't right for you.

225
00:14:50,025 --> 00:14:52,195
And you're not the right man for Ba Ra.

226
00:14:52,325 --> 00:14:53,665
Think about this carefully.

227
00:14:53,965 --> 00:14:55,535
You don't have to explain why.

228
00:14:55,735 --> 00:14:57,205
Don't lead her on.

229
00:14:58,765 --> 00:15:00,875
She's worked hard to rebuild her life.

230
00:15:01,205 --> 00:15:03,645
- She's the one who got to me.
- And I suppose Momo led you?

231
00:15:05,845 --> 00:15:06,845
That is different.

232
00:15:07,675 --> 00:15:10,145
A crush is a crush.
It's all the same thing.

233
00:15:10,645 --> 00:15:11,945
You only think about yourself.

234
00:15:16,055 --> 00:15:18,585
Have I ever done anything to upset you?

235
00:15:21,055 --> 00:15:25,025
If you were to marry our nurse, Lee Shim,
I would go along with it.

236
00:15:26,065 --> 00:15:27,435
Not because I don't value our friendship,

237
00:15:27,865 --> 00:15:30,765
but because that's how much
I'd trust and respect your judgment.

238
00:15:31,835 --> 00:15:33,775
Both you and Ba Ra are important to me.

239
00:15:34,705 --> 00:15:36,305
You're like a brother to me,

240
00:15:36,975 --> 00:15:38,145
and Ba Ra is like a sister.

241
00:15:39,875 --> 00:15:41,015
We're surprisingly compatible.

242
00:15:42,945 --> 00:15:45,445
- That's just your opinion.
- This wasn't an impulsive decision.

243
00:15:45,945 --> 00:15:47,215
I have a really strong feeling about this.

244
00:15:47,455 --> 00:15:49,015
You're the only one feeling it.

245
00:15:49,155 --> 00:15:51,085
Geum Ba Ra is falling for me, too.

246
00:15:52,955 --> 00:15:53,955
Little by little.

247
00:15:55,855 --> 00:15:57,495
Some love is like a rising tide,

248
00:15:58,925 --> 00:16:00,395
but this is like a gentle rain...

249
00:16:01,695 --> 00:16:02,695
that seeps in slowly.

250
00:16:03,435 --> 00:16:04,905
But you're always a rising tide.

251
00:16:05,905 --> 00:16:07,535
And the tide always goes back out.

252
00:16:09,805 --> 00:16:11,075
This time it's really different.

253
00:16:12,675 --> 00:16:14,445
It seems just as impulsive to me.

254
00:16:16,645 --> 00:16:18,145
I'm asking you, seriously,

255
00:16:18,785 --> 00:16:20,555
but don't push her into this.

256
00:16:24,185 --> 00:16:25,425
All right, then let me ask you,
just to be sure.

257
00:16:28,495 --> 00:16:31,695
Do you have any
romantic feelings for Ba Ra?

258
00:16:34,035 --> 00:16:35,095
Think about it carefully.

259
00:16:37,405 --> 00:16:39,435
We're really just like brother and sister,

260
00:16:40,135 --> 00:16:41,205
just not by blood.

261
00:16:43,975 --> 00:16:45,005
All right, then.

262
00:16:52,615 --> 00:16:53,685
Goodness.

263
00:16:56,085 --> 00:16:57,155
Going to bed already?

264
00:16:58,185 --> 00:16:59,355
There's nothing else to do now.

265
00:17:03,595 --> 00:17:05,765
(Missed calls)

266
00:17:07,565 --> 00:17:08,965
(Paul)

267
00:17:10,965 --> 00:17:12,905
(Paul)

268
00:17:14,675 --> 00:17:18,475
(Paul)

269
00:17:18,645 --> 00:17:20,145
(Paul)

270
00:17:34,455 --> 00:17:36,565
(Paul)

271
00:17:49,435 --> 00:17:51,305
Why did you quit the newspaper?

272
00:17:53,475 --> 00:17:54,575
How did you know that?

273
00:17:54,915 --> 00:17:57,485
Your articles stopped,
so I got curious and looked into it.

274
00:17:57,785 --> 00:17:58,985
And I heard you quit.

275
00:18:00,355 --> 00:18:03,185
I'm on a break, helping a close friend.

276
00:18:03,325 --> 00:18:04,485
A close friend?

277
00:18:05,425 --> 00:18:06,425
Momo?

278
00:18:06,995 --> 00:18:08,025
Yes.

279
00:18:08,025 --> 00:18:09,355
Then you must have heard.

280
00:18:15,395 --> 00:18:16,835
I asked Momo...

281
00:18:17,435 --> 00:18:19,235
for a picture of my daughter,

282
00:18:19,905 --> 00:18:20,935
but she said she didn't have any.

283
00:18:20,935 --> 00:18:21,975
You met with her?

284
00:18:22,075 --> 00:18:23,105
Does that make any sense?

285
00:18:25,275 --> 00:18:26,345
It's possible she doesn't.

286
00:18:26,915 --> 00:18:28,875
She might have deleted them
to try to forget.

287
00:18:32,285 --> 00:18:33,785
If you have a picture of my daughter...

288
00:18:36,355 --> 00:18:37,355
You don't have any?

289
00:18:49,965 --> 00:18:51,035
What about a recent one?

290
00:18:51,335 --> 00:18:53,305
We were both busy,
so we didn't see each other often.

291
00:18:54,275 --> 00:18:56,705
So you weren't that close?
So you had a falling out.

292
00:18:59,245 --> 00:19:02,215
Honestly, it still doesn't feel real.

293
00:19:02,215 --> 00:19:03,685
Exactly. Me neither.

294
00:19:05,545 --> 00:19:06,685
How old was she here?

295
00:19:07,185 --> 00:19:08,285
Fourth grade.

296
00:19:11,155 --> 00:19:13,455
- My Jin Ju?
- Yes.

297
00:19:13,795 --> 00:19:15,625
Why were you so tiny, Reporter Geum?

298
00:19:15,895 --> 00:19:16,965
For a fourth grader?

299
00:19:18,225 --> 00:19:19,365
It's not like you were a baby.

300
00:19:26,065 --> 00:19:28,705
Do you really think my Jin Ju is dead?

301
00:19:33,945 --> 00:19:36,515
Considering her body
still hasn't turned up,

302
00:19:37,345 --> 00:19:39,815
I just couldn't believe it,
no matter how hard I tried,

303
00:19:39,815 --> 00:19:41,485
so I went to see a shaman.

304
00:19:42,685 --> 00:19:43,955
She said she was not dead...

305
00:19:45,225 --> 00:19:46,325
and that she was still alive.

306
00:19:52,195 --> 00:19:54,135
I stayed up for two days straight.

307
00:19:55,095 --> 00:19:56,435
I was just so miserable.

308
00:19:57,005 --> 00:19:58,965
I may be a pathetic father,
but I'm still her father.

309
00:19:59,235 --> 00:20:01,575
The only thing keeping me going
was the thought of finding her.

310
00:20:02,735 --> 00:20:05,105
But she thinks she can hide
just because she finds me useless?

311
00:20:06,505 --> 00:20:08,545
The police have closed the investigation.

312
00:20:09,575 --> 00:20:11,485
They're in on it together. Her and Momo.

313
00:20:12,485 --> 00:20:15,155
She's definitely hiding her somewhere.

314
00:20:15,885 --> 00:20:18,385
I heard celebrities own multiple houses.

315
00:20:19,055 --> 00:20:20,655
Do you know where her second home is?

316
00:20:21,255 --> 00:20:22,395
I wouldn't know about that.

317
00:20:23,795 --> 00:20:26,195
Even if you knew,
you wouldn't tell me anyway.

318
00:20:28,835 --> 00:20:31,935
I only heard she has a condo in Jeju,
but I've never been there.

319
00:20:32,265 --> 00:20:33,305
How was...

320
00:20:33,975 --> 00:20:35,535
Momo's relationship with my daughter?

321
00:20:36,775 --> 00:20:37,775
It was...

322
00:20:38,605 --> 00:20:40,045
nothing special.

323
00:20:41,845 --> 00:20:44,085
If she were dead,
why doesn't she appear in my dreams?

324
00:20:45,315 --> 00:20:48,385
Spirits are supposed to visit you
if they're dead.

325
00:20:52,085 --> 00:20:53,225
Then what about the memorial?

326
00:20:54,855 --> 00:20:56,125
It went smoothly.

327
00:21:00,865 --> 00:21:02,565
It was all for nothing then.

328
00:21:14,175 --> 00:21:16,245
Didn't he just dump Momo for Ba Ra?

329
00:21:21,255 --> 00:21:22,555
It's no contest.

330
00:21:23,555 --> 00:21:25,085
I look like such an old man.

331
00:21:26,655 --> 00:21:27,655
James.

332
00:21:35,165 --> 00:21:36,335
You bought this at the airport,
didn't you?

333
00:21:38,105 --> 00:21:39,705
I heard Ju Shin and Ba Ra stopped by.

334
00:21:42,905 --> 00:21:45,205
Ju Shin is totally into Ba Ra.

335
00:21:53,815 --> 00:21:56,355
I'm a pro at reading people,
and I'm sure about this.

336
00:21:59,055 --> 00:22:00,055
What about Ba Ra?

337
00:22:00,525 --> 00:22:01,925
She was just her usual self.

338
00:22:03,525 --> 00:22:05,065
That guy's so unpredictable.

339
00:22:06,025 --> 00:22:07,235
You're not wrong.

340
00:22:10,765 --> 00:22:14,475
Could I give Momo the same treatment
you gave me, Director Shin?

341
00:22:16,745 --> 00:22:17,775
Looks easy, doesn't it?

342
00:22:22,345 --> 00:22:23,845
Explain it to me in detail.

343
00:22:23,945 --> 00:22:25,985
You don't even know if the problem's
in her left or right ear,

344
00:22:26,855 --> 00:22:28,515
or if it's an issue
with the horizontal semicircular canal,

345
00:22:28,955 --> 00:22:30,385
or an abnormality in
the posterior semicircular canal.

346
00:22:31,125 --> 00:22:33,395
If you do it wrong, the crystals could
end up in multiple canals.

347
00:22:33,695 --> 00:22:35,055
And then it gets really complicated.

348
00:22:36,425 --> 00:22:38,025
They say,
"A little knowledge is a dangerous thing."

349
00:22:44,465 --> 00:22:45,605
If you were with me,

350
00:22:46,065 --> 00:22:47,835
you'd never have to worry
about vertigo again.

351
00:23:05,025 --> 00:23:07,955
Reporter Geum's going to end up
marrying the Nua hospital's director.

352
00:23:08,495 --> 00:23:09,925
If I were her, why would I say no?

353
00:23:10,425 --> 00:23:13,865
Right now, she probably feels insecure,
so she can't just say yes right away.

354
00:23:15,165 --> 00:23:16,495
Ba Ra's not a gold digger like that.

355
00:23:16,565 --> 00:23:18,735
It's not being a gold digger.
It's becoming Cinderella.

356
00:23:19,065 --> 00:23:22,675
It's not like he was married.
Was that engagement to Momo a big deal?

357
00:23:23,945 --> 00:23:26,145
Depending on how you look at it,
it's practically a badge of honor.

358
00:23:26,945 --> 00:23:28,675
Beating out a top star like Momo.

359
00:23:28,815 --> 00:23:30,645
Momo would be going crazy with jealousy.

360
00:23:30,715 --> 00:23:33,555
That's probably the main reason
Reporter Geum is hesitating, too.

361
00:23:34,015 --> 00:23:35,055
But still.

362
00:23:42,755 --> 00:23:45,095
They say if you chop at a tree enough,
it's bound to fall.

363
00:23:45,895 --> 00:23:48,365
And knowing Director Shin's personality,
he'd probably chop at it 100 times.

364
00:23:49,365 --> 00:23:50,365
Right?

365
00:24:08,685 --> 00:24:09,815
I can finally breathe.

366
00:24:11,885 --> 00:24:14,025
How could Yong Joong not even
send a text to see if I'm okay?

367
00:24:26,205 --> 00:24:28,235
The shaman said that she wasn't dead?

368
00:24:29,005 --> 00:24:30,005
Yes.

369
00:24:31,905 --> 00:24:34,375
He seems to suspect you of hiding her.

370
00:24:35,015 --> 00:24:36,015
That's crazy.

371
00:24:37,485 --> 00:24:38,485
So what happened?

372
00:24:38,745 --> 00:24:40,455
I heard he asked you for a picture, too.

373
00:24:40,755 --> 00:24:42,915
- Did you give him one?
- An old one I had.

374
00:24:43,555 --> 00:24:45,325
Let me see. Which one did you give him?

375
00:24:48,455 --> 00:24:52,025
I didn't notice it when I first met him,
but his eyes...

376
00:24:53,835 --> 00:24:54,865
are creepy.

377
00:24:56,965 --> 00:24:58,405
He's my enemy, not my father.

378
00:25:02,235 --> 00:25:03,605
What gives him the right?

379
00:25:07,015 --> 00:25:08,375
Search all you want.

380
00:25:09,515 --> 00:25:12,515
Kim Gwang Cheol can run, but I can fly.

381
00:25:26,765 --> 00:25:28,435
That jerk, Shin Ju Shin.

382
00:25:29,395 --> 00:25:32,035
If he'd just fixed this that day,
I wouldn't be going through all this.

383
00:25:41,315 --> 00:25:42,815
The hospital can't really do
much for you, right?

384
00:25:43,175 --> 00:25:45,915
- Right.
- They just taught you some exercises.

385
00:25:46,185 --> 00:25:47,185
Right.

386
00:25:48,715 --> 00:25:50,115
I asked Ba Ra to marry me.

387
00:25:52,325 --> 00:25:53,325
When?

388
00:25:55,625 --> 00:25:56,725
So, what did she say?

389
00:25:57,195 --> 00:25:58,225
She said no.

390
00:25:58,995 --> 00:26:00,025
How could you...

391
00:26:02,565 --> 00:26:03,635
Are you out of your mind?

392
00:26:04,965 --> 00:26:06,005
Watch your mouth.

393
00:26:06,105 --> 00:26:07,935
How long has it been
since our breakup article?

394
00:26:08,075 --> 00:26:09,175
And her, of all people?

395
00:26:10,205 --> 00:26:12,405
- Geum Ba Ra is a better choice.
- How is she better?

396
00:26:12,475 --> 00:26:14,445
Stop talking nonsense out of spite.

397
00:26:14,715 --> 00:26:17,345
Should I just pull my hair back
and expose that I'm Kim Jin Ju?

398
00:26:17,645 --> 00:26:19,785
- Go ahead.
- What do you think would happen then?

399
00:26:20,385 --> 00:26:21,455
Is that a threat?

400
00:26:22,585 --> 00:26:24,925
Your biological father, Kim Gwang Cheol,
would be the first one to come running.

401
00:26:25,785 --> 00:26:27,255
And what do you think the world would say?

402
00:26:28,025 --> 00:26:29,625
He's still your biological father,
after all.

403
00:26:31,225 --> 00:26:32,295
For a daughter to do such a thing.

404
00:26:35,265 --> 00:26:36,865
In this situation, it's a win-win for us.

405
00:26:36,935 --> 00:26:39,765
What's in it for me?
What does that make me?

406
00:26:41,335 --> 00:26:42,605
This is so humiliating.

407
00:26:43,205 --> 00:26:46,005
People will forget soon enough.
You just have to find someone better.

408
00:26:47,075 --> 00:26:48,115
Just like that?

409
00:26:49,715 --> 00:26:50,715
You're Momo, after all.

410
00:26:54,115 --> 00:26:56,955
In life, if you try hard enough,
you can pretty much get what you want.

411
00:26:57,025 --> 00:26:58,755
Why Geum Ba Ra of all people?

412
00:26:59,985 --> 00:27:02,695
I know Geum Ba Ra better than you do.

413
00:27:04,095 --> 00:27:07,035
You're getting way ahead of yourself.
Ba Ra would never...

414
00:27:11,835 --> 00:27:14,735
Don't jinx it. Put in a good word for me.

415
00:27:16,435 --> 00:27:17,645
Think about all I've done for you.

416
00:27:21,345 --> 00:27:24,245
I turned Cinderella Kim Jin Ju
into the superstar Momo.

417
00:27:24,785 --> 00:27:28,085
I sometimes miss
my old body and my old face.

418
00:27:31,325 --> 00:27:33,185
You want me to change your face back
to look like Kim Jin Ju?

419
00:27:34,555 --> 00:27:35,725
I can get it pretty close.

420
00:27:42,395 --> 00:27:44,105
- You're here.
- Yes.

421
00:28:05,425 --> 00:28:06,985
Should I ask him
about that shaman's house?

422
00:28:10,155 --> 00:28:12,295
No, he might get suspicious
if I bring it up.

423
00:28:12,865 --> 00:28:14,595
Have you been well, Mr. Kim?

424
00:28:15,265 --> 00:28:16,535
It's Geum Ba Ra.

425
00:28:24,805 --> 00:28:26,975
I'm afraid all I have to offer
is green tea.

426
00:28:33,445 --> 00:28:36,285
Your paintings always make me
feel so warm.

427
00:28:37,425 --> 00:28:38,455
Pick one out.

428
00:28:38,785 --> 00:28:40,495
I'd rather work hard
and earn the money to buy one.

429
00:28:42,355 --> 00:28:44,595
I can tell you genuinely love my work.

430
00:28:45,925 --> 00:28:47,295
That's why I want to give you one.

431
00:28:47,295 --> 00:28:49,235
Then let's do a gift exchange later.

432
00:28:51,165 --> 00:28:52,965
I was traveling, starting from Namhae,

433
00:28:53,265 --> 00:28:55,335
and an artist friend
in Boryeong made me stay,

434
00:28:55,335 --> 00:28:56,635
so I was there for two days.

435
00:28:57,505 --> 00:28:59,875
- The artist, Hong Seon Hui.
- I know her.

436
00:29:00,075 --> 00:29:02,145
She's single, just like you.

437
00:29:02,945 --> 00:29:05,215
Her painting style is very dynamic.

438
00:29:05,415 --> 00:29:08,985
Yes, and she's as strong and free-spirited
as her art.

439
00:29:09,385 --> 00:29:11,025
The youngest daughter
of the Seven Princesses' House.

440
00:29:11,085 --> 00:29:12,585
Because her parents were hoping for a son?

441
00:29:13,255 --> 00:29:14,255
Yes.

442
00:29:16,355 --> 00:29:17,765
Next August...

443
00:29:17,825 --> 00:29:20,535
Yes.
That's plenty of time to prepare, right?

444
00:29:20,595 --> 00:29:22,565
I might have to go to Germany.

445
00:29:23,295 --> 00:29:24,865
Do you have an exhibition?

446
00:29:25,035 --> 00:29:29,135
In Korea, he'd be my older cousin brother
on my father's side.

447
00:29:29,905 --> 00:29:31,275
He always really looked out for me.

448
00:29:31,605 --> 00:29:32,705
But...

449
00:29:34,175 --> 00:29:36,045
he was diagnosed with cancer.

450
00:29:36,545 --> 00:29:39,385
- Oh, no.
- He's started chemo,

451
00:29:41,115 --> 00:29:42,515
but I feel like I need to go see him.

452
00:29:45,485 --> 00:29:49,655
Of course.
We'll send a special invitation to you.

453
00:29:51,195 --> 00:29:52,465
Is Momo...

454
00:29:53,025 --> 00:29:54,235
doing well?

455
00:29:55,495 --> 00:29:56,495
Yes.

456
00:29:56,965 --> 00:29:58,135
Tell her I said hi.

457
00:29:58,635 --> 00:29:59,635
I will.

458
00:29:59,935 --> 00:30:02,135
I guess you don't come
to Seoul very often.

459
00:30:02,205 --> 00:30:03,435
Every once in a while...

460
00:30:05,075 --> 00:30:06,575
That must be our curator.

461
00:30:11,315 --> 00:30:12,515
The local market was open,

462
00:30:12,515 --> 00:30:14,155
so I did some browsing
and bought a few things.

463
00:30:16,055 --> 00:30:18,125
And I stopped by Jangichu
for these coffee beans.

464
00:30:19,185 --> 00:30:20,355
You shouldn't have.

465
00:30:20,425 --> 00:30:22,395
Perfect timing.
He was just saying he ran out of coffee.

466
00:30:24,025 --> 00:30:27,735
Get that troublesome Ba Ra out of the way
by giving her to Shin Ju Shin?

467
00:30:28,495 --> 00:30:30,635
As they say, "The ends justify the means."

468
00:30:31,305 --> 00:30:34,735
If I want Ha Yong Joong,
it might be better if Ba Ra is married.

469
00:30:40,005 --> 00:30:43,175
How can I stand by and watch her become
the Nua Foundation chairman's wife?

470
00:30:46,085 --> 00:30:48,585
Shin Ju Shin... Ha Yong Joong...

471
00:30:49,455 --> 00:30:52,855
Ha Yong Joong is so much more personable
and manly.

472
00:31:04,865 --> 00:31:08,035
What if my brain were in Ba Ra's body?

473
00:31:13,005 --> 00:31:14,245
Ba Ra...

474
00:31:14,645 --> 00:31:17,075
She's only had eyes for Ha Yong Joong,

475
00:31:17,345 --> 00:31:19,045
so she won't open up to someone else.

476
00:31:19,415 --> 00:31:21,185
And believe it or not,
she's got her pride.

477
00:31:22,815 --> 00:31:25,785
Your mother has been managing
the artists so well,

478
00:31:25,855 --> 00:31:28,895
so I think the exhibition
will go off without a hitch.

479
00:31:29,755 --> 00:31:30,925
Why didn't you tell me?

480
00:31:32,425 --> 00:31:34,195
Why did I have to hear it
from Director Shin?

481
00:31:36,865 --> 00:31:38,265
There's no reason for you to refuse.

482
00:31:38,865 --> 00:31:40,335
I never even considered it.

483
00:31:40,605 --> 00:31:43,945
I made myself perfectly clear,
so I didn't need to bring it up.

484
00:31:43,945 --> 00:31:45,075
But he seemed so sure of himself.

485
00:31:46,005 --> 00:31:47,345
You know me.

486
00:31:48,075 --> 00:31:49,075
Don't you?

487
00:31:50,415 --> 00:31:54,585
It's not exactly normal for Director Shin
to ask you to marry him, is it?

488
00:31:57,385 --> 00:31:58,625
Deep down, are you tempted?

489
00:32:03,855 --> 00:32:06,165
- You never know with people's hearts.
- Time will tell.

490
00:32:07,465 --> 00:32:09,735
So it's Ha Yong Joong and no one else?

491
00:32:11,705 --> 00:32:14,935
We need to find a new curator, fast.
Jeong Ah is moving to the US.

492
00:32:15,035 --> 00:32:16,905
Her husband got transferred
to the LA branch.

493
00:32:18,045 --> 00:32:19,545
Maybe I should just close the gallery.

494
00:32:20,945 --> 00:32:21,945
It's overwhelming.

495
00:32:23,675 --> 00:32:26,745
You're on leave anyway.
Just have fun doing whatever you want,

496
00:32:26,815 --> 00:32:28,155
and then go back to your job
at the newspaper.

497
00:32:28,555 --> 00:32:30,455
I'll keep you on the payroll
for a few more months.

498
00:32:35,125 --> 00:32:37,425
You're coming with us to Singapore
next month, right?

499
00:32:37,765 --> 00:32:39,165
Singapore? What for?

500
00:32:41,435 --> 00:32:42,535
Haven't you heard?

501
00:32:42,535 --> 00:32:44,635
"A Maiden's Prayer"
has become a massive sleeper hit.

502
00:32:44,765 --> 00:32:45,805
For a fan meeting.

503
00:32:46,865 --> 00:32:47,975
That's great.

504
00:32:49,305 --> 00:32:50,945
But I don't really have to go, do I?

505
00:32:51,545 --> 00:32:54,375
But Singapore is so nice.
They have great food too.

506
00:33:13,865 --> 00:33:15,665
(Yong Joong)

507
00:33:16,465 --> 00:33:17,465
When are you getting here?

508
00:33:18,035 --> 00:33:19,335
Waiting for you in an empty house.

509
00:33:27,305 --> 00:33:28,875
Even if you're not interested,

510
00:33:29,245 --> 00:33:30,615
when someone confesses
their feelings like that,

511
00:33:32,315 --> 00:33:34,385
I bet you could start to develop them.

512
00:33:36,755 --> 00:33:38,355
It wasn't exactly a confession.

513
00:33:38,955 --> 00:33:41,025
Frankly, I don't get Director Shin either.

514
00:33:41,855 --> 00:33:44,925
You know Ju Shin.
He's not the type to give up easily.

515
00:33:46,025 --> 00:33:47,025
No.

516
00:33:47,595 --> 00:33:49,765
He's not the type
to get needlessly obsessed.

517
00:33:49,895 --> 00:33:51,465
Because of that pride of his.

518
00:33:53,835 --> 00:33:57,075
I just have to meet him
and make myself clear again.

519
00:34:00,475 --> 00:34:01,615
What do you think?

520
00:34:03,045 --> 00:34:04,885
You're the one who said
I should find a good man, right?

521
00:34:06,215 --> 00:34:08,055
As a doctor, he's perfect,

522
00:34:08,855 --> 00:34:10,315
but Ju Shin is
not exactly marriage material.

523
00:34:10,825 --> 00:34:12,885
He's not the type
to go all-in for a woman.

524
00:34:14,425 --> 00:34:15,755
He admits it himself.

525
00:34:18,265 --> 00:34:19,265
And you?

526
00:34:20,465 --> 00:34:22,765
You're the type who would go all-in
for a woman?

527
00:34:30,375 --> 00:34:32,905
How can anyone be perfect
and good at everything?

528
00:34:35,275 --> 00:34:38,315
- Are you making excuses for him?
- It's not an excuse, it's the truth.

529
00:34:39,945 --> 00:34:41,755
Now that you've gotten an offer like that,

530
00:34:42,655 --> 00:34:43,655
are you swayed?

531
00:34:48,025 --> 00:34:49,925
Where did your pride go, Geum Ba Ra?

532
00:34:51,825 --> 00:34:54,635
That was just pride born from insecurity.

533
00:34:56,365 --> 00:34:58,235
It's from fighting and winning
your battles,

534
00:34:58,635 --> 00:35:00,135
the self-respect from doing your best.

535
00:35:00,405 --> 00:35:02,835
You're the one who has lived that way.

536
00:35:04,005 --> 00:35:06,105
Though you do fall apart
when it comes to Momo.

537
00:35:07,075 --> 00:35:08,315
What are you talking about?

538
00:35:11,085 --> 00:35:12,215
So are you saying you're against it?

539
00:35:13,545 --> 00:35:15,655
I'm worried you'll end up like Momo.

540
00:35:15,785 --> 00:35:17,055
Is that the only reason?

541
00:35:17,455 --> 00:35:20,325
Ju Shin's an old friend,
but honestly, I'm worried about you.

542
00:35:21,095 --> 00:35:22,255
What am I, a child?

543
00:35:22,395 --> 00:35:24,825
Geum Ba Ra needs to be happy from now on.

544
00:35:25,625 --> 00:35:27,225
And she deserves every bit of it.

545
00:35:28,495 --> 00:35:31,205
- How?
- By finding a much better guy.

546
00:35:39,745 --> 00:35:40,805
Don't worry.

547
00:35:41,475 --> 00:35:43,845
He's just the son of the chairman
I'm indebted to.

548
00:35:44,345 --> 00:35:45,645
Just the director.

549
00:35:56,555 --> 00:35:57,565
Got any drinks?

550
00:35:58,295 --> 00:36:01,465
I had a few bottles of wine,
but I gave them as gifts to some writers.

551
00:36:01,595 --> 00:36:02,595
We can just order some.

552
00:36:05,335 --> 00:36:06,335
Or should we go out?

553
00:36:28,725 --> 00:36:32,095
Why didn't you visit Momo in the hospital?
I'm sure you wanted to.

554
00:36:32,825 --> 00:36:33,925
Is she okay now?

555
00:36:35,095 --> 00:36:36,165
She's been discharged.

556
00:36:36,465 --> 00:36:38,535
There wasn't much the hospital
could do for her anyway.

557
00:36:40,565 --> 00:36:41,675
You want the honest truth?

558
00:36:44,075 --> 00:36:45,345
It didn't even cross my mind.

559
00:36:45,905 --> 00:36:46,975
I completely forgot.

560
00:36:47,915 --> 00:36:48,915
You're lying.

561
00:36:49,215 --> 00:36:50,345
I'm serious.

562
00:36:50,345 --> 00:36:51,945
I only remembered when you mentioned it.

563
00:36:54,085 --> 00:36:55,515
Were you that busy?

564
00:36:56,115 --> 00:36:59,125
It seems Ju Shin rushed to the karaoke bar
that day, thinking it was you.

565
00:36:59,255 --> 00:37:01,595
I'm a guy too, but it is what it is.

566
00:37:02,055 --> 00:37:04,025
You really can't trust people's feelings.

567
00:37:06,425 --> 00:37:08,595
But some feelings never change.

568
00:37:09,835 --> 00:37:11,235
Like mine.

569
00:37:12,205 --> 00:37:13,305
Like you.

570
00:37:14,305 --> 00:37:15,375
I wouldn't know about that.

571
00:37:16,835 --> 00:37:18,545
What about the marketing head's funeral?

572
00:37:18,975 --> 00:37:20,105
It went as well as it could.

573
00:37:20,845 --> 00:37:22,275
It must've been so devastating.

574
00:37:22,415 --> 00:37:24,445
It means while we're alive,

575
00:37:25,015 --> 00:37:26,315
we really have to live without regrets.

576
00:37:27,115 --> 00:37:29,685
We have to do our best
for the people by our side...

577
00:37:30,285 --> 00:37:31,355
and love them.

578
00:37:34,125 --> 00:37:35,625
You, of course...

579
00:37:37,095 --> 00:37:39,065
I said you were my number one, right?

580
00:37:39,325 --> 00:37:41,295
You'll marry who's before number one.

581
00:37:43,735 --> 00:37:45,805
Why is this soju
going down so smoothly today?

582
00:37:46,135 --> 00:37:47,705
It's giving me a perfect buzz.

583
00:37:48,235 --> 00:37:49,235
Look at you changing the subject.

584
00:37:49,235 --> 00:37:51,175
I'm not changing the subject.

585
00:37:52,145 --> 00:37:53,345
That hurt!

586
00:37:56,175 --> 00:37:58,085
And here I thought I was the only one
who found you pretty.

587
00:37:59,545 --> 00:38:01,555
But since it was you,
you didn't fall for it.

588
00:38:03,315 --> 00:38:06,485
Ju Shin would make a move on any woman
he had a connection to.

589
00:38:07,025 --> 00:38:09,025
Classmates from med school,
underclassmen, you name it.

590
00:38:09,125 --> 00:38:12,025
You get tons of calls
from matchmakers too, don't you?

591
00:38:12,125 --> 00:38:14,695
And I hear plenty of women
hit on you at bars and places.

592
00:38:14,765 --> 00:38:15,795
When did I ever tell you that?

593
00:38:16,065 --> 00:38:17,465
James did.

594
00:38:19,005 --> 00:38:20,265
I have to be the one who's interested.

595
00:38:20,975 --> 00:38:22,175
Most guys are like that.

596
00:38:23,105 --> 00:38:26,505
So that means I have absolutely no chance.

597
00:38:26,575 --> 00:38:27,945
According to Ju Shin,

598
00:38:28,515 --> 00:38:29,745
you two are a good match.

599
00:38:32,215 --> 00:38:35,255
We can hold a conversation, I guess.
That's about it.

600
00:38:35,515 --> 00:38:37,015
From now on, only talk to me.

601
00:38:37,355 --> 00:38:39,385
You can only ramble on in front of me.

602
00:38:40,425 --> 00:38:44,225
I guess I'll ramble with you
and talk politely with Director Shin.

603
00:38:45,065 --> 00:38:46,095
What's gotten into you?

604
00:38:46,095 --> 00:38:47,465
What about you?

605
00:38:47,565 --> 00:38:48,735
What's wrong with me?

606
00:38:48,995 --> 00:38:51,435
You know I'm always on your side,
no matter what.

607
00:38:51,505 --> 00:38:52,805
Spare me the lip service.

608
00:38:53,205 --> 00:38:54,375
I mean it.

609
00:38:58,705 --> 00:39:00,875
If it weren't for his history with Momo,

610
00:39:01,315 --> 00:39:04,175
I might've actually considered
giving the Director a chance.

611
00:39:05,385 --> 00:39:06,985
So you are attracted to him.

612
00:39:08,285 --> 00:39:09,515
You're saying you're attracted to him.

613
00:39:10,715 --> 00:39:12,385
It's scary how
you can get attached to people.

614
00:39:13,455 --> 00:39:14,625
You've gotten attached?

615
00:39:16,695 --> 00:39:18,565
He was intimidating, and it was awkward.

616
00:39:19,325 --> 00:39:22,365
But now, I somehow feel as comfortable
with him as I do with you.

617
00:39:26,135 --> 00:39:28,035
Some paths aren't meant to be taken.

618
00:39:28,575 --> 00:39:30,475
It will only end in heartbreak,
just like with Momo.

619
00:39:32,805 --> 00:39:34,345
Momo's the one who ended it.

620
00:39:35,315 --> 00:39:36,445
And so he hits her?

621
00:39:36,715 --> 00:39:39,145
You never hit a woman. Ever.

622
00:39:39,485 --> 00:39:40,745
There's absolutely no excuse.

623
00:39:43,815 --> 00:39:47,225
You must have been so heartbroken,
hearing how he hit her.

624
00:39:48,195 --> 00:39:51,095
If he'd done that to you,
I would've half-killed Ju Shin.

625
00:39:55,595 --> 00:39:58,835
You have me,
so you can do whatever you want...

626
00:40:00,035 --> 00:40:03,205
and live your life
with your head held high.

627
00:40:03,835 --> 00:40:05,305
My whole life?

628
00:40:11,445 --> 00:40:14,115
Are you going to find me a good man
and marry me off?

629
00:40:14,755 --> 00:40:16,685
Honestly, that's not going to be easy.

630
00:40:16,985 --> 00:40:18,985
You know how people say
men are all animals?

631
00:40:19,625 --> 00:40:21,595
There's not a single decent guy
I know to recommend.

632
00:40:24,155 --> 00:40:28,165
You're a different breed from most guys.

633
00:40:32,005 --> 00:40:33,735
So am I a 90...

634
00:40:34,335 --> 00:40:35,375
out of 100.

635
00:40:36,135 --> 00:40:37,235
Straight A's.

636
00:40:37,775 --> 00:40:39,005
In every way.

637
00:40:44,375 --> 00:40:46,215
You won't find another angel like me.

638
00:40:49,185 --> 00:40:50,355
You have no idea.

639
00:40:51,155 --> 00:40:53,055
I can be pretty wicked
in my head sometimes.

640
00:40:53,685 --> 00:40:55,455
It's okay if you get wicked.

641
00:40:55,495 --> 00:40:57,325
And I have pointless thoughts, too.

642
00:40:57,925 --> 00:40:59,095
What kind of pointless thoughts?

643
00:41:00,395 --> 00:41:02,935
Guys probably don't daydream like this.

644
00:41:03,295 --> 00:41:05,365
They say people in Korea run
on the power of rice,

645
00:41:06,935 --> 00:41:09,305
but I've always run
on the power of my fantasies.

646
00:41:09,475 --> 00:41:11,845
Isn't that just dreaming, not fantasizing?

647
00:41:12,175 --> 00:41:13,745
A plan. An ambition.

648
00:41:19,585 --> 00:41:23,455
If you could turn my fantasy
into reality for me,

649
00:41:24,655 --> 00:41:25,825
that would be wonderful.

650
00:41:36,995 --> 00:41:38,005
Tell me.

651
00:41:39,105 --> 00:41:40,105
Anything.

652
00:41:44,645 --> 00:41:45,875
What is it?

653
00:41:48,315 --> 00:41:51,585
Have you heard of
"What day? Monday, birthday?"

654
00:41:52,545 --> 00:41:54,415
No, but I feel like I should.

655
00:41:54,415 --> 00:41:55,885
If you do, you're an old man.

656
00:41:56,255 --> 00:41:57,685
Age-wise, I guess I am.

657
00:41:58,285 --> 00:41:59,955
Your face is nothing like an old man's.

658
00:42:03,295 --> 00:42:06,665
I'll tell you after I finish my drink
and lose my filter.

659
00:42:16,475 --> 00:42:17,475
I think I know.

660
00:42:18,145 --> 00:42:20,275
You wanted to be a dancer, not a reporter.

661
00:42:20,945 --> 00:42:22,815
You said you only backup danced
at karaoke bars.

662
00:42:26,645 --> 00:42:28,985
I think I've had the perfect amount
to drink today.

663
00:42:30,785 --> 00:42:31,825
You should go.

664
00:42:34,025 --> 00:42:35,025
I don't want to.

665
00:42:37,655 --> 00:42:40,325
I like this vibe. It's so comfortable.

666
00:42:43,535 --> 00:42:44,965
I want to keep talking.

667
00:42:51,875 --> 00:42:52,875
I love you.

668
00:42:53,905 --> 00:42:55,015
Me too.

669
00:42:55,815 --> 00:42:57,045
Don't copy me.

670
00:42:57,315 --> 00:42:59,185
After today, don't say
"I love you" anymore.

671
00:42:59,915 --> 00:43:01,145
I'll be the only one to say it.

672
00:43:05,325 --> 00:43:07,255
- Yong Joong.
- Yes?

673
00:43:09,295 --> 00:43:10,695
School clubs...

674
00:43:11,895 --> 00:43:13,395
You only took
the high school equivalency exam, right?

675
00:43:13,865 --> 00:43:16,835
- Are you talking about college clubs?
- Yes. I was in the dance club.

676
00:43:17,065 --> 00:43:18,065
I've got some moves.

677
00:43:18,065 --> 00:43:20,235
If it wasn't for Momo's vertigo that day,

678
00:43:20,605 --> 00:43:22,405
I would've gotten to see
my baby's dance moves.

679
00:43:24,705 --> 00:43:26,205
Don't call me "baby" today.

680
00:43:32,045 --> 00:43:33,945
Here you go, Princess.

681
00:43:44,025 --> 00:43:46,225
The reason that
I joined the dance club was...

682
00:43:48,335 --> 00:43:49,495
You know how in foreign movies,

683
00:43:50,435 --> 00:43:54,135
- brides do a father-daughter dance.
- Yes.

684
00:43:54,265 --> 00:43:57,275
But no matter how many times I marry,
I won't have a dad to dance with.

685
00:43:58,805 --> 00:44:00,345
But I still wanted to learn how.

686
00:44:01,275 --> 00:44:02,515
I guess I felt like something was missing.

687
00:44:05,185 --> 00:44:06,985
If he's even alive out there,

688
00:44:09,255 --> 00:44:11,355
or if he's already passed on.

689
00:44:23,395 --> 00:44:26,565
Tonight, don't think of me
as your brother.

690
00:44:27,865 --> 00:44:29,575
Think of me as your dad.

691
00:44:32,705 --> 00:44:34,105
But I can't dance.

692
00:44:48,455 --> 00:44:49,555
Just feel the rhythm.

693
00:47:00,585 --> 00:47:01,755
I love you, Yong Joong.

694
00:47:02,555 --> 00:47:03,555
I love you.

695
00:48:10,195 --> 00:48:11,665
Where are you headed?

696
00:48:12,995 --> 00:48:14,795
The tech show. Going to the conference?

697
00:48:14,795 --> 00:48:16,995
Yes. The one in Las Vegas?

698
00:48:23,335 --> 00:48:24,335
(Text Message)

699
00:48:31,715 --> 00:48:33,715
(Momo: Hello.
Sorry, I've had my phone turned off.)

700
00:48:33,885 --> 00:48:37,285
Hello.
Sorry, I've had my phone turned off.

701
00:48:45,795 --> 00:48:46,795
(Text Message)

702
00:48:49,195 --> 00:48:50,295
Are you free to talk?

703
00:48:52,065 --> 00:48:53,465
(Paul)

704
00:48:57,435 --> 00:48:58,445
Hello?

705
00:48:58,945 --> 00:49:00,745
What? Was he some Korean guy?

706
00:49:02,015 --> 00:49:03,675
He has a nice voice, though.

707
00:49:04,575 --> 00:49:05,585
Hello?

708
00:49:05,945 --> 00:49:06,945
It's been a while.

709
00:49:07,585 --> 00:49:08,585
Yes.

710
00:49:08,615 --> 00:49:11,955
I read that Kim Jin Ju went missing,
and I thought about calling you...

711
00:49:12,085 --> 00:49:13,325
Who is this? How does he know me?

712
00:49:13,925 --> 00:49:15,725
We should get a meal sometime
when you're free.

713
00:49:16,755 --> 00:49:19,325
Sure. I'm free these days.

714
00:49:19,425 --> 00:49:22,135
Send me a few dates that work for you,
and I'll pick a place and text you.

715
00:49:22,695 --> 00:49:23,695
How about tomorrow?

716
00:49:33,475 --> 00:49:34,945
I wonder who he is...

717
00:49:34,945 --> 00:49:36,075
Good, I'm not late.

718
00:49:36,875 --> 00:49:38,045
I hit traffic right as I was getting here.

719
00:49:39,945 --> 00:49:41,045
Hello.

720
00:49:41,545 --> 00:49:43,555
- Yes.
- Is a table by the window okay?

721
00:49:51,055 --> 00:49:52,325
No way... It's him?

722
00:49:54,865 --> 00:49:57,265
Are you Kim Young Jun, by any chance?

723
00:49:57,695 --> 00:49:59,105
What about the name Kim Jin Ju?

724
00:49:59,435 --> 00:50:02,335
It's just what I was named,
and what I've always been called.

725
00:50:04,605 --> 00:50:06,405
- I'll have the same.
- Okay.

726
00:50:07,545 --> 00:50:09,145
So how does he know Momo?

727
00:50:09,415 --> 00:50:10,575
I've been worried about you.

728
00:50:11,545 --> 00:50:12,885
You seem better than I thought.

729
00:50:13,085 --> 00:50:14,645
I'm not really.

730
00:50:15,955 --> 00:50:18,855
I think the shock from everything
that happened was too much,

731
00:50:19,285 --> 00:50:20,885
making my memory spotty.

732
00:50:21,455 --> 00:50:25,325
My doctor says it's temporary amnesia...

733
00:50:27,765 --> 00:50:28,765
Really?

734
00:50:29,435 --> 00:50:30,435
Yes.

735
00:50:31,065 --> 00:50:33,205
So you don't remember me either?

736
00:50:35,305 --> 00:50:36,675
Not exactly.

737
00:50:39,045 --> 00:50:40,405
So tell me already.

738
00:50:41,745 --> 00:50:45,145
You called me after your mom
told you the whole story.

739
00:50:46,485 --> 00:50:47,485
I did?

740
00:50:49,285 --> 00:50:52,285
We had met before that at an exhibition.
You were with Geum Ba Ra, the reporter.

741
00:50:55,255 --> 00:50:56,495
What whole story?

742
00:50:58,225 --> 00:50:59,725
What story are you talking about?

743
00:51:02,065 --> 00:51:03,065
It's just...

744
00:51:03,995 --> 00:51:07,235
It's not important, so don't worry
about it if you can't remember.

745
00:51:07,305 --> 00:51:08,905
No, please tell me.

746
00:51:10,735 --> 00:51:12,005
Please, I'm asking.

747
00:51:12,375 --> 00:51:15,645
My memories are all jumbled up,
and I can't sleep well.

748
00:51:40,665 --> 00:51:41,665
Yes, Mr. Ha.

749
00:51:41,975 --> 00:51:43,535
Does Pickles have a regular vet?

750
00:51:44,205 --> 00:51:46,405
- Why?
- He had diarrhea a few times yesterday,

751
00:51:46,405 --> 00:51:48,205
and now he won't eat and is lethargic.

752
00:51:50,575 --> 00:51:51,645
Thank you.

753
00:51:51,915 --> 00:51:53,515
Just switch his food
and he should be fine.

754
00:51:53,945 --> 00:51:56,385
- Okay.
- Come on, let's go.

755
00:51:59,755 --> 00:52:00,925
First off, congratulations.

756
00:52:01,325 --> 00:52:03,625
I heard from Yong Joong.
It's definitely something to celebrate.

757
00:52:06,295 --> 00:52:08,195
I know Director Shin better than anyone.

758
00:52:08,865 --> 00:52:10,735
And I'm the one
who introduced him to Momo.

759
00:52:11,065 --> 00:52:12,435
But it just wasn't meant to be.

760
00:52:14,065 --> 00:52:17,305
Just accept your good fortune.
You'll regret it if you let him go.

761
00:52:19,505 --> 00:52:21,745
Think of it as a blessing from the sky.

762
00:52:22,315 --> 00:52:24,475
Even if you had unlucky parents,
you can be lucky in marriage.

763
00:52:25,285 --> 00:52:27,785
And if you lack both, the deity will
bless you with good children, right?

764
00:52:28,615 --> 00:52:29,955
I was lucky to have
good adoptive parents...

765
00:52:29,955 --> 00:52:32,285
- I...
- What a nice day.

766
00:52:33,325 --> 00:52:35,225
Oh my, what breed is that?

767
00:52:36,895 --> 00:52:39,095
- I'll tell you later.
- I'll just order something.

768
00:52:39,165 --> 00:52:40,795
- Okay.
- Alright.

769
00:52:41,725 --> 00:52:44,165
- What breed is your dog?
- He's a White Terrier.

770
00:52:44,395 --> 00:52:45,735
He looks familiar.

771
00:52:46,035 --> 00:52:47,505
She's a dog model, Agati.

772
00:52:47,505 --> 00:52:50,275
- No wonder. She's so beautiful.
- You can just tell, can't you?

773
00:52:50,275 --> 00:52:52,445
Yes, I knew she looked like a model.

774
00:52:52,975 --> 00:52:54,575
Oh my, she's so gorgeous.

775
00:52:54,975 --> 00:52:55,975
Hi there.

776
00:53:15,865 --> 00:53:16,965
(International Flights)

777
00:53:18,565 --> 00:53:21,005
(Las Vegas, Landed)

778
00:53:55,835 --> 00:53:57,735
You already spent so much
time on me today.

779
00:54:04,375 --> 00:54:06,745
I will next time
when my hands aren't so cold.

780
00:54:07,815 --> 00:54:10,155
Why are your hands cold? Are you cold?

781
00:54:10,415 --> 00:54:13,555
I just have that type of body.
My body gets cold if I don't eat beef.

782
00:54:15,925 --> 00:54:17,555
Did you have a pleasant flight?

783
00:54:19,665 --> 00:54:20,665
I did, thank you.

784
00:54:29,675 --> 00:54:30,975
The doors are closing.

785
00:54:32,705 --> 00:54:34,475
Now that you mention it,
I vaguely remember...

786
00:54:36,575 --> 00:54:39,185
So, that means I have an older sister...

787
00:54:48,455 --> 00:54:51,295
So that's CEO Hyun's dirty little secret?

788
00:54:51,995 --> 00:54:55,835
Jin Ju, your hair is so lovely and thick.

789
00:54:57,735 --> 00:54:58,735
Mom.

790
00:55:00,365 --> 00:55:01,835
She ran a DNA test.

791
00:55:02,435 --> 00:55:03,635
To see if, by any chance,
I was her daughter.

792
00:55:12,385 --> 00:55:15,685
So she faked her death and went to him
pretending to be Momo.

793
00:55:17,115 --> 00:55:20,685
I wonder if my birth mother
ever thinks about me.

794
00:55:22,255 --> 00:55:23,855
She must, if she's even human.

795
00:55:26,425 --> 00:55:28,425
Why did she have to fall
for a guy like that?

796
00:55:28,765 --> 00:55:30,095
If she had a kid,
she should've taken responsibility.

797
00:55:30,965 --> 00:55:34,505
You know the saying.
"Live together, die together."

798
00:55:35,165 --> 00:55:36,505
On top of that,
to abandon your own flesh and blood...

799
00:55:45,745 --> 00:55:46,745
Ms. Ba Ra is here.

800
00:55:51,685 --> 00:55:52,785
(Korean beef)

801
00:55:57,125 --> 00:56:00,365
(Korean beef)

802
00:56:00,565 --> 00:56:02,965
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

803
00:56:07,965 --> 00:56:09,005
(Message from Geum Ba Ra)

804
00:56:09,075 --> 00:56:11,875
Director Shin,
are you back from the conference?

805
00:56:12,445 --> 00:56:14,205
Why did you send so much Korean beef...

806
00:56:14,375 --> 00:56:19,285
(Stock up...)

807
00:56:20,915 --> 00:56:25,385
(Geum Ba Ra)

808
00:56:29,095 --> 00:56:30,095
Hello?

809
00:56:31,525 --> 00:56:32,795
I don't have time for a meal,

810
00:56:33,725 --> 00:56:34,795
but can we meet up for a bit?

811
00:56:35,125 --> 00:56:36,135
I'm on my way.

812
00:56:36,665 --> 00:56:37,665
I like that.

813
00:56:38,565 --> 00:56:40,765
No arguing, no excuses.

814
00:56:41,205 --> 00:56:43,575
There's a nice cafe
in front of the hospital...

815
00:56:43,905 --> 00:56:44,905
Do you know it?

816
00:56:51,915 --> 00:56:52,915
Hi.

817
00:56:57,885 --> 00:56:59,225
What did Yong Joong get you for a gift?

818
00:57:00,685 --> 00:57:01,685
A bracelet.

819
00:57:03,455 --> 00:57:04,455
Why aren't you wearing it?

820
00:57:05,255 --> 00:57:06,795
It doesn't go with my outfit.

821
00:57:07,425 --> 00:57:09,465
I couldn't find anything to buy
under the 600 dollar limit.

822
00:57:09,765 --> 00:57:11,295
It's not like you were on a trip
or anything.

823
00:57:11,765 --> 00:57:13,365
And it makes the receiver
feel awkward, too.

824
00:57:30,515 --> 00:57:32,585
A surgery drained me.

825
00:57:48,405 --> 00:57:49,635
Hey, we're matching today.

826
00:57:52,205 --> 00:57:53,345
See? We're on the same wave.

827
00:57:54,275 --> 00:57:56,075
A whole box of meat...

828
00:57:56,545 --> 00:57:58,115
Are you always this generous?

829
00:57:58,375 --> 00:57:59,785
It will last me for six months.

830
00:57:59,945 --> 00:58:02,415
What are you talking about?
That's a month's worth.

831
00:58:02,415 --> 00:58:03,485
Grill some every day.

832
00:58:05,785 --> 00:58:07,585
Cold hands mean a cold body.

833
00:58:09,155 --> 00:58:10,955
- Any constipation?
- Sometimes?

834
00:58:12,155 --> 00:58:13,925
I make sure to eat enough fiber.

835
00:58:15,895 --> 00:58:16,965
Didn't you miss me?

836
00:58:19,905 --> 00:58:20,905
You did think of me, right?

837
00:58:23,275 --> 00:58:24,275
Yes.

838
00:58:25,705 --> 00:58:27,175
Shouldn't you be heading back in?

839
00:58:32,345 --> 00:58:33,345
Five more minutes.

840
00:58:47,065 --> 00:58:48,325
Don't get sick.

841
00:58:49,265 --> 00:58:50,935
Worried you'll have to come make me
bean sprout soup?

842
00:58:51,595 --> 00:58:52,765
That's nothing too hard.

843
00:58:55,265 --> 00:58:56,335
Are your hands warmer now?

844
00:58:57,605 --> 00:58:59,105
I'll have to grill some
for dinner tonight.

845
00:58:59,575 --> 00:59:01,905
- Alone?
- Should I throw a party?

846
00:59:02,105 --> 00:59:03,715
Medicine doesn't work if you share it.

847
00:59:03,845 --> 00:59:05,215
And don't drink cold things like this.

848
00:59:06,085 --> 00:59:08,785
- You too, Director Shin.
- I'm drinking this to wake myself up.

849
00:59:11,085 --> 00:59:12,485
How long are you going to keep
calling me Director Shin?

850
00:59:14,085 --> 00:59:15,755
It's because you're the director.

851
00:59:17,495 --> 00:59:18,495
Are you one of my patients?

852
00:59:21,825 --> 00:59:23,035
Go on up to the penthouse and wait.

853
00:59:23,895 --> 00:59:25,295
What am I supposed to do there?

854
00:59:25,735 --> 00:59:29,335
You could do a home workout,
or surprise me with a delicious meal.

855
00:59:30,475 --> 00:59:31,535
I'll be done with my rounds around eight.

856
00:59:33,805 --> 00:59:35,545
Since you were so thoughtful to send it,

857
00:59:35,815 --> 00:59:37,415
I'd like to go try some
before I have to freeze it.

858
00:59:39,745 --> 00:59:40,815
Make sure to send me a picture.

859
00:59:41,285 --> 00:59:42,285
Okay.

860
00:59:54,865 --> 00:59:56,995
You didn't eat lunch because of surgery,
did you?

861
00:59:57,135 --> 00:59:58,165
How could I be the only one to eat?

862
01:00:03,735 --> 01:00:06,575
If your mother were still alive,
her heart would break for you.

863
01:00:06,645 --> 01:00:08,445
We all work just to put food
in our mouths.

864
01:00:10,875 --> 01:00:11,875
Does your heart ache for me?

865
01:00:19,585 --> 01:00:20,855
Look at me like that
every once in a while.

866
01:00:21,625 --> 01:00:22,625
I like that look in your eyes.

867
01:00:28,265 --> 01:00:29,335
You should go first.

868
01:00:29,635 --> 01:00:30,635
Why?

869
01:00:30,935 --> 01:00:33,905
We're right in front of the hospital.
Your staff or patients might see us.

870
01:00:33,965 --> 01:00:36,075
So what? What does it matter?

871
01:00:38,535 --> 01:00:40,275
I'm going to get this to go.

872
01:00:47,515 --> 01:00:49,385
I'll think of you every time
I have an Americano.

873
01:00:50,555 --> 01:00:52,055
I'll be thinking of you today, too,
Director Shin.

874
01:00:52,955 --> 01:00:54,455
This is a weird way to put it,

875
01:00:55,125 --> 01:00:56,425
but you were actually kind of cute.

876
01:00:56,695 --> 01:00:58,455
It was a side of you
I never would have imagined.

877
01:01:00,995 --> 01:01:01,995
If I catch a cold,

878
01:01:02,565 --> 01:01:03,565
will you wipe my nose for me too?

879
01:01:06,105 --> 01:01:07,105
Don't work too hard.

880
01:01:12,645 --> 01:01:14,305
- Can I get this to go?
- Sure.

881
01:01:38,735 --> 01:01:40,005
(Momo)

882
01:01:43,635 --> 01:01:45,335
- Yes?
- Did you have to propose to Ba Ra...

883
01:01:45,335 --> 01:01:46,545
and scare her away?

884
01:01:47,145 --> 01:01:49,615
- Scare her away?
- She said she's going abroad.

885
01:01:50,645 --> 01:01:53,615
- When?
- She said goodbye to me yesterday.

886
01:01:56,355 --> 01:01:58,285
- For a trip?
- A trip? I don't think so.

887
01:01:59,955 --> 01:02:02,655
She claims she's going to study,
but that's just what she's saying.

888
01:02:02,725 --> 01:02:05,895
She's leaving to escape you.
What other reason could there be?

889
01:02:07,725 --> 01:02:08,725
I'm hanging up.

890
01:02:37,195 --> 01:02:39,695
(Geum Ba Ra)

891
01:02:47,735 --> 01:02:49,275
(Geum Ba Ra)

892
01:02:54,505 --> 01:02:55,505
Yes, Director Shin.

893
01:02:57,145 --> 01:02:58,145
Can I join you?

894
01:02:58,575 --> 01:03:00,245
I'll cook some for you sometime.

895
01:03:00,645 --> 01:03:03,315
- The meat's no good once it's cold.
- "Sometime"?

896
01:03:04,685 --> 01:03:05,685
Yes.

897
01:03:07,025 --> 01:03:08,025
I'm at your front door.

898
01:03:12,525 --> 01:03:15,765
I came unannounced.
So I can't be mad if you turn me away.

899
01:03:19,505 --> 01:03:20,505
Should I just leave?

900
01:03:25,075 --> 01:03:26,075
Let yourself in.

901
01:03:49,665 --> 01:03:50,735
Where can I wash my hands?

902
01:04:12,215 --> 01:04:13,225
Have a seat.

903
01:04:14,825 --> 01:04:15,925
There's no soup.

904
01:04:17,855 --> 01:04:20,465
It's a stir-fried red pepper paste
made with the sirloin you bought me.

905
01:04:23,535 --> 01:04:25,265
My mom used to make this for me sometimes.

906
01:04:28,935 --> 01:04:29,935
I'll mix it in with my rice.

907
01:04:30,975 --> 01:04:33,145
- Why are you getting up?
- Sesame oil.

908
01:04:33,205 --> 01:04:34,205
No.

909
01:04:34,745 --> 01:04:35,745
I want to taste the red pepper paste.

910
01:04:39,145 --> 01:04:40,415
You didn't mention
you were going on a trip.

911
01:04:41,345 --> 01:04:42,585
I mean, I just saw you a few hours ago.

912
01:04:43,955 --> 01:04:45,855
I was going to email you...

913
01:04:46,485 --> 01:04:47,485
since you're so busy.

914
01:04:50,025 --> 01:04:51,095
And I knew it'd be a long conversation.

915
01:04:52,325 --> 01:04:53,325
Where are you going?

916
01:04:56,695 --> 01:04:58,935
- Is it a secret?
- It's not a secret.

917
01:04:59,365 --> 01:05:01,135
I might move around once I get there.

918
01:05:03,405 --> 01:05:04,405
Does Yong Joong know?

919
01:05:04,805 --> 01:05:05,805
Yes.

920
01:05:15,115 --> 01:05:16,115
My appetite's coming back.

921
01:05:16,715 --> 01:05:17,715
I had no appetite at all before.

922
01:05:25,225 --> 01:05:27,065
- Any wine?
- I don't have any.

923
01:05:27,495 --> 01:05:28,725
Dip it in the sesame oil sauce.

924
01:05:39,305 --> 01:05:41,005
Let's sit here for a bit.

925
01:05:42,375 --> 01:05:43,945
Goodness.

926
01:05:45,075 --> 01:05:46,085
Pickles.

927
01:05:46,745 --> 01:05:48,345
Your mom was glowing.

928
01:05:49,355 --> 01:05:51,185
I suppose it's because
she was proposed to.

929
01:06:03,735 --> 01:06:07,405
What if I die without ever getting
to propose to a woman?

930
01:06:09,935 --> 01:06:11,805
It's embarrassing
getting called a grandfather...

931
01:06:11,805 --> 01:06:12,905
when I'm still a bachelor.

932
01:06:22,315 --> 01:06:25,615
You know the passcode, right?
Have an employee get the leftover meat.

933
01:06:26,085 --> 01:06:27,525
Is Yong Joong paying for your trip?

934
01:06:27,885 --> 01:06:28,885
No.

935
01:06:29,285 --> 01:06:31,055
I worked hard and saved the money myself.

936
01:06:31,555 --> 01:06:32,865
I have enough to last me a few years.

937
01:06:33,965 --> 01:06:34,965
Why are you leaving?

938
01:06:35,465 --> 01:06:37,365
- Just because.
- That's not fair.

939
01:06:50,745 --> 01:06:52,075
Can't you be honest with me?

940
01:06:52,545 --> 01:06:54,845
But you're the one who said
being too honest is rude.

941
01:06:57,755 --> 01:06:58,815
Later...

942
01:07:00,155 --> 01:07:02,455
I'll tell you when I'm ready.

943
01:07:05,725 --> 01:07:07,025
Is there something I don't know?

944
01:07:16,835 --> 01:07:18,605
I'm not ready to talk about it yet.

945
01:07:19,105 --> 01:07:21,245
Momo says it's because of me.

946
01:07:22,705 --> 01:07:24,015
That you feel pressured because of me.

947
01:07:24,015 --> 01:07:25,515
It's not because of you, Director Shin.

948
01:07:28,285 --> 01:07:29,285
What does Yong Joong say?

949
01:07:31,215 --> 01:07:33,585
He doesn't meddle in my affairs.

950
01:07:38,155 --> 01:07:39,155
There's...

951
01:07:40,265 --> 01:07:41,895
someone I like.

952
01:07:44,065 --> 01:07:45,335
That's why I'm leaving.

953
01:07:52,535 --> 01:07:53,545
Who is it?

954
01:07:55,905 --> 01:07:57,615
I'm sorry...

955
01:07:58,875 --> 01:07:59,945
for not telling you sooner.

956
01:08:07,385 --> 01:08:08,385
Show me a picture.

957
01:08:09,225 --> 01:08:10,325
You must have one.

958
01:08:10,455 --> 01:08:11,555
Then I'll believe you.

959
01:08:11,895 --> 01:08:13,725
As a final favor, please don't press me.

960
01:08:15,325 --> 01:08:17,335
I'd rather not say anything right now.

961
01:08:17,865 --> 01:08:20,565
I'll email you once I'm settled in.

962
01:08:24,335 --> 01:08:25,405
And this isn't just an excuse?

963
01:08:26,405 --> 01:08:27,405
For real?

964
01:08:29,105 --> 01:08:30,115
Yes.

965
01:08:42,255 --> 01:08:43,355
Is it Yong Joong?

966
01:08:53,765 --> 01:08:54,765
I knew it.

967
01:09:06,215 --> 01:09:07,415
But why are you leaving?

968
01:09:10,255 --> 01:09:11,315
There's nothing more...

969
01:09:13,625 --> 01:09:15,125
I have to say.

970
01:09:19,095 --> 01:09:20,525
We're just supposed to end it here
like this?

971
01:09:20,525 --> 01:09:21,565
No questions asked?

972
01:09:22,625 --> 01:09:23,765
Although we never started anything...

973
01:09:34,275 --> 01:09:37,075
He told you to just quietly pack up
and leave Korea?

974
01:09:45,585 --> 01:09:46,585
What is it?

975
01:09:52,355 --> 01:09:53,365
Take a deep breath.

976
01:09:58,095 --> 01:09:59,095
Breathe in deeply.

977
01:10:01,135 --> 01:10:02,135
Please, go.

978
01:10:05,105 --> 01:10:06,405
(Nua General Hospital)

979
01:10:08,545 --> 01:10:09,815
Send an ambulance, now.

980
01:10:11,675 --> 01:10:12,845
In front of Jaeil Apartments,
Building 102.

981
01:10:15,285 --> 01:10:16,285
Please...

982
01:10:19,655 --> 01:10:20,725
Just go.

983
01:10:21,455 --> 01:10:22,455
Don't talk.

984
01:10:24,895 --> 01:10:25,895
Want me to give you mouth-to-mouth?

985
01:11:19,115 --> 01:11:21,885
(Doctor Shin)

986
01:11:22,145 --> 01:11:23,885
The numbers are higher than I thought.

987
01:11:23,885 --> 01:11:24,985
Were you okay while I was gone?

988
01:11:31,095 --> 01:11:33,225
(She is eating well.)

989
01:11:33,325 --> 01:11:35,265
Pretend it's champagne and drink it.

990
01:11:35,325 --> 01:11:36,395
Let's set a wedding date.

991
01:11:36,965 --> 01:11:38,235
I hope you like it.

992
01:11:39,235 --> 01:11:40,235
I'm at a loss for words.

993
01:11:40,905 --> 01:11:42,865
- That won't solve anything.
- Hello?

994
01:11:42,935 --> 01:11:44,275
- Yong Joong.
- Yes?

995
01:11:44,405 --> 01:11:45,475
Thank you.

996
01:11:45,475 --> 01:11:47,175
I made a promise to volunteer...

997
01:11:47,675 --> 01:11:48,845
to the Blessed Virgin Mary.

998
01:11:51,015 --> 01:11:53,145
Tell me what you're craving.

999
01:11:53,285 --> 01:11:55,815
My mom always made a full spread
with at least five side dishes.

1000
01:11:55,815 --> 01:11:56,855
You're not up for that, are you?

1001
01:11:56,915 --> 01:11:58,915
- I'll give it a shot.
- Have you ever seen Ba Ra dance?

1002
01:11:58,985 --> 01:12:00,755
No, why?

1003
01:12:00,755 --> 01:12:02,685
You don't marry someone out of pity.

1004
01:12:02,755 --> 01:12:03,955
It's not pity.

1005
01:12:04,255 --> 01:12:06,095
I guess you'll have to make my dress.

1006
01:12:06,155 --> 01:12:08,525
- For which embassy party?
- My wedding dress.

1007
01:12:09,425 --> 01:12:10,495
Really?

1008
01:12:10,695 --> 01:12:11,935
No way!

1009
01:12:14,965 --> 01:12:16,975
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
